<a href="https://hackclub.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="corner-flag" aria-label="Hack Club">
  <img src="https://assets.hackclub.com/flag-orpheus-top.svg" alt="Hack Club flag">
</a>

<main class="page">
  <div class="card">
    <div class="header">
      <div class="logo" aria-label="TheHackGrant logo">
        <img class="layer blob" src="/propel1.png" alt="">
        <img class="layer glow" src="/propel4.png" alt="">
        <img class="layer dino" src="/propel2.png" alt="">
        <img class="layer rocket" src="/propel3.png" alt="">
      </div>
      <p class="brand">TheHackGrant</p>
    </div>

    <h1>
      <span class="amount">$50&ndash;$200</span> to build something cool.
    </h1>

    <p class="sub">
      A microgrant from Hack Club for anyone under 18. Hardware or software.
      Log your hours, ship your project, and join thousands of others in the
      Hack Club database.
    </p>

    <div class="actions">
      <%= link_to "Apply now", "/submit", class: "apply" %>
      <a href="https://hackclub.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="link">What&rsquo;s Hack Club? &rarr;</a>
    </div>

    <div class="faq" data-controller="faq">
      <button class="q" data-faq-target="button" data-action="click->faq#toggle">Who can apply?</button>
      <p class="a" data-faq-target="answer" hidden>Anyone under 18. That&rsquo;s the only requirement.</p>

      <button class="q" data-faq-target="button" data-action="click->faq#toggle">What can I build?</button>
      <p class="a" data-faq-target="answer" hidden>
        Hardware or software. A keyboard, a website, a game, a robot, a
        browser extension, a 3D-printed thing. If you&rsquo;re not sure, apply
        anyway.
      </p>

      <button class="q" data-faq-target="button" data-action="click->faq#toggle">How does the money work?</button>
      <p class="a" data-faq-target="answer" hidden>
        Between $50 and $200, sent to you through Hack Club&rsquo;s grant
        infrastructure. Your spending gets auto-logged so you don&rsquo;t have
        to keep receipts. Buy parts, pay for hosting, register a domain,
        and it shows up on your project page.
      </p>

      <button class="q" data-faq-target="button" data-action="click->faq#toggle">What&rsquo;s the catch?</button>
      <p class="a" data-faq-target="answer" hidden>
        You log hours as you work on the project. It&rsquo;s how we know you&rsquo;re
        actually building something, and it lets you see your own progress
        over time. No long timesheets. Just a quick check-in when you sit
        down to work.
      </p>

      <button class="q" data-faq-target="button" data-action="click->faq#toggle">What&rsquo;s the Hack Club database?</button>
      <p class="a" data-faq-target="answer" hidden>
        Hack Club runs a unified database of thousands of teen projects
        from Summer of Making, Highway, Athena, and dozens of other
        programs. Your grant project lives there too, alongside everyone
        else&rsquo;s. You can browse what other teens are building and they can
        find yours.
      </p>

      <button class="q" data-faq-target="button" data-action="click->faq#toggle">What happens at the end?</button>
      <p class="a" data-faq-target="answer" hidden>
        You ship it. Wrap up the build, post the project page, share a
        demo or repo link. Shipping is the requirement. Even if it&rsquo;s
        small, broken, or weird, it has to actually exist.
      </p>

      <button class="q" data-faq-target="button" data-action="click->faq#toggle">When do I hear back?</button>
      <p class="a" data-faq-target="answer" hidden>Applications are rolling. We try to reply within two weeks.</p>
    </div>

    <p class="footer">
      An initiative by <a href="https://hackclub.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hack Club</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</main>
